{
  "text": "The microphone (resp. speaker) nonlinearity introduces higher-order correlations at its output. The MSM processing chain, therefore, can be modeled using a higher-order nonlinear system. To capture it HOSA is used. Specifically, higher-order cumulants (resp. bicoherence) [CITATION_1] is used to capture higher-order correlations. The bicoherence, , of a signal y[n] is a normalized version of 2-dimensional Fourier transform of the third-order cumulants, that is, Here, denotes third-order cumulant of y[n], and is defined as, Here, E{.} denotes expectation. Sometimes, it is more convenient to use the normalized value of the bispectrum which is also known as bicoherence. This bicoherence is given by the following equation [CITATION_2] ,",
